pageTitle: ETSUBucs.com - Men’s soccer clipped by Davidson in 2OT, 2-1
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {14019=Saturday, September 15, 2012, 18283=ETSU dominated the first session, putting five shots at Pacifici and taking four corners, but never found the back of the net and moved on to the second extra session. With 8:35 to play, Paras lined up the free kick following a Buccaneer foul to earn the Wildcats their third victory of the season., 14464=Valeriy Svidersky leveled the match with 10:04 to play in regulation off a long free kick from the other side of midfield, and Davidson’s (3-2-1) Ryan Malden was issued his second yellow to be sent off with four minutes to go. It proved to work against ETSU as Paras lined up for a free kick from 20 yards in the second overtime, driving a shot off a diving Ryan Coulter’s (Dublin, Ireland) glove and into the back of the net for the win.}
